<BaseLayout title="What is Campbellocking?">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="page-label">Foundations</p>

    <h1>What is Campbellocking?</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="essay-section">
    <h2>It all started with Don Campbell</h2>

    <p>
      "Campbellocking", commonly known as Locking, is a Funk dance inspired by
      the movements and improvisations of Don Campbell.
    </p>

    <p>
      In 1970, Don Campbell was attempting to learn a party dance known as "The
      Robot Shuffle". Unable to execute the dance smoothly, his movements began
      to take on a different form — pauses, freezes, and rhythmic stops that
      would later become known as "The Lock".
    </p>

    <p>
      Don's dancing quickly gained attention. As people began copying his
      movements, a new dance started to emerge. Over time, this evolved into the
      dance now known worldwide as Campbellocking, or simply Locking.
    </p>

    <p>
      The dance later gained international visibility through appearances by The
      Lockers on television programmes such as Soul Train, helping spread
      Locking and Funk culture globally.
    </p>

    <p>
      For a more detailed explanation of Campbellocking history, visit the
      <a href="https://campbellock.dance/" target="_blank">
        official Campbellocking website</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
